				<td colspan="2"><span>Hm.. I never really liked the Troubadours mace, seeing as how it goes for 10-12k. And for that you can buy some better stuff. That and I never really minded the swapping since I dont AE kite much, usually Swarm.
<br />

<br />
Though other things Id say would be to sell the iksar mask (depending on what you get, brell they sell for 8K). With that you could buy a copper hammer of striking, or a sword of the bloodsworn. And that reminds me, do your epic aswell.
<br />

<br />
Do you have LDoN? If so do some adventures, at 56 you should get about 30 points per adventure, and most groups will love a bard. Go on an LDoN, get points in the camp of your choice, and buy some items/augs. Heres a site with the listing of all LDoN items, their camp, and their price, so you can decide where to go. <i><b>http://www.cardplace.com/eq/ldon/list.cgi</b></i> That and the split from an LDoN Adventure is usually 50-100pp, plus the points, plus the decent EXP.
<br />

<br />
Hope it helps... and I would get GoD. Natimbi exp is really nice, and I soloed the Mace in about 6 hours to get all 4 essences. Probably luck, since Ive heard people spend days, but eh.</span></td>
