			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: 56 bard with horrible gear... somebody help me please!<a name="42728"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">May 27 04 3:53 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I LOVE dulak for farming...I even do it at lvl 65
<br />

<br />
Auto-circling is extremely simple here, the ground is completely level throughout the docks area. For information regarding auto-circle AEing, look to the bard solo section of the forums here.
<br />

<br />
As deeply said you can pick up 40-60 in coin from a kite easily, but thats not where the money comes from. The pirates can drop gems worth up to raw diamond level ~170pp with good cha, and jewelry pieces worth up to 90-100pp.
<br />

<br />
My usual farming pattern in dulak (assuming its empty as it usually is on my server, except the boats):
<br />

<br />
1) Entrance mobs, the little DE female, human male pirates standing around the entrance and in the first large area. I usually pick up a guardian or two and a blackhand, this makes for about 24-26 mobs.
<br />

<br />
2) I pick up all the mobs in the two warehouses right across the large open space to the right as you walk in from zone in. These mobs hit hard and might be difficult to pull for lower level bards, I get hurt maybe 10-20% trying to pull them, so take caution. This usually pulls around 20-25 mobs.
<br />

<br />
3) Kite 3 is my favorite, here I run past the guards at the amory and inside the armory I pick up everything, usually takes a few passes for me(since they are green/lightblue). These mobs hit the hardest of all the kites and getting stunned can actually hurt pretty bad even at 65. Only times I've died are to the armory mobs due to a little lag on the auto-circle. Usual pull nets 30-32 mobs. The higher level ones here are the ones that drop raw diamond.
<br />

<br />
4) Next pull is the shipyard which is right by the armory, head out of the armory and turn left following the wall you will pick up little gnomes and trolls. run around this little area and pick up what you can find here. One caveat to this place is there is a single caster here, cleric type. She is a static spawn at the little bridge over to Windscorn. She will cast Retribution(~500 dd nuke) but hasnt tried to root me ever. I usually ignore her if she adds into my pull but lower lvl bards might want to avoid pulling her at all. The Windscorn pirates have the most HP, but I find them poor for farming purposes. The shipyard pull is usually in the neighborhood of 23-25 mobs, more if you pick up the ship yard mobs standing out near armory.
<br />

<br />
5) At this point, depending on your kill speed, the entrance mobs are most likly respawned for you to go back and start the farm loop over. Or, if you want you can continue on to the warehouses directly across from shipyard and also Shady house, which is a house of 4 or 5 Shady Treasure Sorters, which drop the waterlogged lute for our LoY bard song, Aria of Innocence(or maybe its the other one /bonk). 
<br />

<br />
After this I will start my farming routine over.
<br />

<br />
Don't bother pulling boats, I did for a while and all it does is lag the zone crazy with the poor pathing multiplied by 20 pirates running crazy after you. Besides it can be very dangerous for lower lvl bards.
<br />

<br />
If you do the auto-circling AE kite there is one small thing to be weary of, when you loot so many corpses, you will eventually become weighed down, thus slowing your speed. Even the slight speed reduction due to weight WILL affect auto-circling, your circle becomes smaller, thus the mobs are more likely to hit/stun you. I am not a greedy person, but even I over-do it sometimes in dulak :p. 
<br />

<br />
Now when I go I destroy all the copper/silver every once in a while. Also, when the gold reaches 1300-1400 I get ready to go on a sell run. I no longer loot anything <u>except</u> weapons, gems, jewelry, blood, meat and equipment(from nameds that pop infrequently). 
<br />

<br />
The blood/meat/equipment will sell in the bazaar well, over the course of one evening I could probably loot enough blood/meat to sell for 1-1.5k in bazaar, sells fast as well. Equipment is a little harder to sell. Shields that drop sell for ~5pp each, but they are GIANT slot, so unless you have a lot of giant slots open, I'd recommend filling up on weapons instead. Did I mention bring a LOT of bags?
<br />

<br />
When I do this I usually net anywhere between 2300-2700pp in one run usually taking maybe an hour and 15 minutes per run(this is SEVERELY affected by your kill rate, which depends on level and instrument modifier). And that figure doesn't include what I make over-night through bazaar mule on meat/blood. Do this constantly for a few days, maybe over a weekend and you can earn enough to buy whatever you need.
<br />

<br />
Sorry to all the people out there that didn't want this information divulged, but I figure it could be helpful to other bards since we're the only ones 'good' enough to farm efficiently here<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" />
<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />
** BAH This post got out of hand, sorry about the long read **</span></td>
