				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: 56 bard with horrible gear... somebody help me please!<a name="43371"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jun 1 04 9:07 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Tarein,
<br />

<br />
Here is how I start auto-circle without getting beat on:
<br />

<br />
*I assume you have collected your mass of victims*
<br />

<br />
0) make sure your in third person, helicopter camera mode so you can see your relative distance from mobs
<br />

<br />
1) run a few manual circles to get them all bunched up and &quot;stacked&quot; together in a neat little group.
<br />

<br />
2) this part takes some practice, run a manual, tighter circle. as soon as you would normally STOP turning(to go straight again) hit enter twice, release the arrow/movement keys.
<br />

<br />
If done right, you will see your character go straight for a second then turn into a smooth circle with mobs in tow. After a couple times I never got hit on starting auto-circle(pretty important when auto-circling mobs like HoH guardians). Its not as hard as it may sound.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="SmallText"><hr size="1" align="left" width="15%"><A href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=844375">Reilna Voiceofwar</A><br>

"Be a bard's bard!"</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
